Narrator: Vina, Estela and I sat in Palas Rez...

Vina, Estela and I sat in Palas Rezna's most ornate stateroom, awaiting the arrival of Queen Beatrice Livingston.

LineNo: 10527912,

Pabel Adria: Announcing Her Majesty Beatrice Li...
en


"Announcing Her Majesty Beatrice Livingston, Queen of the Four Corners of Merkopa, Defender of Castle Tzarsbough, Conqueror of the Tranquil Sea, Stout Protector of the Ancient Lands of Rum, Descendant of the Most Honorable King Edward the First and the Ruler of Rumburg.‚Äù

LineNo: 10528014,

Narrator: Pabel came in through the stateroom...
en


Pabel came in through the stateroom door. He took a deep breath.

LineNo: 10528116,

Narrator: He stepped aside and Queen Beatrice...
en


He stepped aside and Queen Beatrice entered. She was wearing an emerald-green gown that matched her tiara.

LineNo: 10528218,

Narrator: Vina, Estela and I rose to greet th...
en


Vina, Estela and I rose to greet the queen.

LineNo: 10528344,

Player_Romus_Italic: I kissed my sister-in-law on the ch...
en


I kissed my sister-in-law on the cheek. She returned the gesture warmly.

LineNo: 10528350,

Player_Romus_Italic: I kissed my sister-in-law on the ch...
Menu Text en


Kiss Beatrice on the cheek.

LineNo: 10528452,

Player_Romus_Italic: I took my sister-in-law's hand and...
en


I took my sister-in-law's hand and kissed it. She looked me up and down.

LineNo: 10528458,

Player_Romus_Italic: I took my sister-in-law's hand and...
Menu Text en


Kiss her hand.

Player_Romus_Italic: I shook my sister-in-law's hand. Sh...
en


I shook my sister-in-law's hand. She returned it with a firm grip.

LineNo: 10528566,

Player_Romus_Italic: I shook my sister-in-law's hand. Sh...
Menu Text en


Shake her hand.

LineNo: 10528668,

Player_Romus_Italic: I gave my sister-in-law a hug. She...
en


I gave my sister-in-law a hug. She returned it warmly.

LineNo: 10528674,

Player_Romus_Italic: I gave my sister-in-law a hug. She...
Menu Text en


Embrace her.

LineNo: 10528776,

Beatrice Livingston (R): What a pleasure it is to see you,...
en


"What a pleasure it is to see you, Your Majesty. We barely had the chance to speak at the coronation."

LineNo: 10528878,

Beatrice Livingston (R): And my dear niece!
en


"And my dear niece!"

LineNo: 10528980,

Narrator: She turned towards Vina.
en


She turned towards Vina.

LineNo: 10529082,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Why, you're looking more and more...
en


"Why, you're looking more and more like your mother every day. I hope your father's proud of the lady you've become."

LineNo: 10529200,

Narrator: Beatrice embraced her tightly befor...
en


Beatrice embraced her tightly before moving on to my mother.

LineNo: 10529302,

Estela Toras: Queen Beatrice.
en


"Queen Beatrice."

LineNo: 10529404,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Queen Mother Estela.
en


"Queen Mother Estela."

LineNo: 10529506,

Narrator: She tilted her face upwards and gav...
en


She tilted her face upwards and gave a short sniff.

LineNo: 10529608,

Beatrice Livingston (R): The palace looks as magnificent as...
en


"The palace looks as magnificent as always, but I fear a chat with your housekeeper may be in order. Every time I visit, it smells just the faintest bit like trash."

LineNo: 10529710,

Estela Toras: Funny, I do seem to detect an unpl...
en


"Funny, I do seem to detect an unpleasant draft of hot air. But only since you walked in."

LineNo: 10529828,

Player_Romus: Let's be civil, ladies. We have im...
en


"Let's be civil, ladies. We have important state issues to discuss."

LineNo: 10529930,

Player_Romus: Shall we be seated?
en


"Shall we be seated?"

LineNo: 10530032,

Player_Romus: Pabel, please look into these matt...
en


"Pabel, please look into these matters at once. The air quality in the palace may be compromised."

LineNo: 10530134,

Narrator: Pabel bemusedly raised an eyebrow.
en


Pabel bemusedly raised an eyebrow.

LineNo: 10530236,

Pabel Adria: Right away, Your Majesty.
en


"Right away, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10530338,

Estela Toras: Then I shall take my leave. I have...
en


"Then I shall take my leave. I have a terribly urgent appointment on the other side of the palace."

LineNo: 10530440,

Estela Toras: If you'll excuse me, I shall take...
en


"If you'll excuse me, I shall take my leave. I have a terribly urgent appointment on the other side of the palace."

LineNo: 10530542,

Beatrice Livingston (R): By all means, Your Highness. Our c...
en


"By all means, Your Highness. Our chatter is far more boring than the sort of carousing you're used to."

LineNo: 10530644,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Vina, why don't you run along as w...
en


"Vina, why don't you run along as well? We'll catch up over supper."

LineNo: 10530746,

Narrator: Vina reluctantly nodded.
en


Vina reluctantly nodded.

LineNo: 10530848,

Vina Toras: Sure, Aunt Bea. Have the staff giv...
en


"Sure, Aunt Bea. Have the staff give my room a ring when you're done."

LineNo: 10530950,

Narrator: He filled two porcelain cups for us...
en


He filled two porcelain cups for us, then escorted Vina and my mother out the door.

LineNo: 10531052,

Player_Romus: Queen Mother Estela may have a com...
en


"Queen Mother Estela may have a common upbringing, but she's part of the royal family. Please respect her as such."

LineNo: 10531154,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Whatever do you mean, my love?
en


"Whatever do you mean, my love?"

LineNo: 10531256,

Player_Romus: How is your own family?
en


"How is your own family?"

LineNo: 10531358,

Player_Romus: To what do we owe this pleasure, Y...
en


"To what do we owe this pleasure, Your Excellency?"

LineNo: 10531460,

Player_Romus_Italic: I took a sip of Rumburgian tea. Len...
en


I took a sip of Rumburgian tea. Lena had loved its earthy taste, but I never quite got used to it.

LineNo: 10531466,

Player_Romus_Italic: I took a sip of Rumburgian tea. Len...
Menu Text en


Sip your tea.

LineNo: 10531568,

Beatrice Livingston (R): First things first.
en


"First things first."

LineNo: 10531670,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Splendid. King Consort Boris sends...
en


"Splendid. King Consort Boris sends his sincerest regrets. He had to oversee some air force exercises."

LineNo: 10531772,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Of course we are the same age, You...
en


"Of course we are the same age, Your Majesty, but I've worn my crown for many years longer than you have yours."

LineNo: 10531874,

Beatrice Livingston (R): And I and my country are far more...
en


"And I and my country are far more experienced at dealing with the Republic of Wehlen and their backers in the CSP."

LineNo: 10532254,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Sending your own investigators to...
en


"Sending your own investigators to ferret out the bombing culprit is a good start. It shows President Smolak you are unwilling to play by his terms."

LineNo: 10532634,

Beatrice Livingston (R): By indicating that you regard your...
en


"By indicating that you regard your own countrymen as culpable for the bombing, you are putting yourself in a position of weakness from the start."

LineNo: 10532736,

Beatrice Livingston (R): By apologizing to President Smolak...
en


"By apologizing to President Smolak for a perfectly justified speech, you are putting yourself in a position of weakness from the start."

LineNo: 10532838,

Beatrice Livingston (R): But how do you plan to follow that...
en


"But how do you plan to follow that up? What will you do if Mr. Smolak fails to relinquish his hold on Zille?"

LineNo: 10532964,

Player_Romus: That won't happen. President Smola...
en


"That won't happen. President Smolak will respect the rule of law."

LineNo: 10533066,

Player_Romus: If it comes down to it, I'm prepar...
en


"If it comes down to it, I'm prepared to fight."

LineNo: 10533168,

Player_Romus: We will exercise diplomacy until a...
en


"We will exercise diplomacy until an agreement is reached."

LineNo: 10533270,

Player_Romus: I know Rumburg has its own agenda...
en


"I know Rumburg has its own agenda when it comes to Wehlen. Rizia's path will be different."

LineNo: 10533372,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Our only agenda is neutralizing th...
en


"Our only agenda is neutralizing the threat that this unpredictable regime poses to its neighbors. Including you."

LineNo: 10533474,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Then you will need Rumburg's help.
en


"Then you will need Rumburg's help."

LineNo: 10533600,

Beatrice Livingston (R): To that end, Rumburg is prepared t...
en


"To that end, Rumburg is prepared to provide assistance with the delicate situation in which you've found yourself."

LineNo: 10533726,

Beatrice Livingston (R): That sounds simply wonderful, Your...
en


"That sounds simply wonderful, Your Majesty. Until you arrive at the bargaining table and realize your pockets are empty."

LineNo: 10533828,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Have you thought about your next s...
en


"Have you thought about your next steps? What will you do if Mr. Smolak fails to relinquish his hold on Zille?"

LineNo: 10534510,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You denied that your countrymen we...
en


"You denied that your countrymen were culpable for the attack. But you must realize President Smolak will not take your words at face value."

LineNo: 10534612,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You have expressed no opinion on t...
en


"You have expressed no opinion on the incident thus far. You must realize that President Smolak will see that as an admission of guilt."

LineNo: 10534984,

Player_Romus: I'm already funding a Rizian cultu...
en


"I'm already funding a Rizian cultural organization in Zille. That should get locals on my side."

LineNo: 10535086,

Beatrice Livingston (R): A good monarch is prepared for eve...
en


"A good monarch is prepared for every eventuality. No matter how unlikely he or she believes it is."

LineNo: 10535188,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I see. A light touch.
en


"I see. A light touch."

LineNo: 10535290,

Narrator: Beatrice leaned forward and held my...
en


Beatrice leaned forward and held my gaze.

LineNo: 10535392,

Player_Romus: I thought this was a family visit,...
en


"I thought this was a family visit, Your Excellency. Can we save the politics for another time?"

LineNo: 10535494,

Player_Romus: You've helped us so much over the...
en


"You've helped us so much over the years. I would not ask more of you."

LineNo: 10535596,

Player_Romus: Do go on, Queen Beatrice.
en


"Do go on, Queen Beatrice."

LineNo: 10535698,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You don't need to ask.
en


"You don't need to ask."

LineNo: 10536078,

Narrator: She shot me a piercing glance. I wo...
en


She shot me a piercing glance. I wondered how much Lena had told her.

LineNo: 10536180,

Narrator: She looked at me with what seemed l...
en


She looked at me with what seemed like genuine compassion.

LineNo: 10536282,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Here's what I suggest, Your Majest...
en


"Here's what I suggest, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10536384,

Pabel Adria: I'll see you two out. Just a momen...
en


"I'll see you two out. Just a moment."

LineNo: 10536486,

Narrator: Pabel walked Beatrice and myself ov...
en


Pabel walked Beatrice and myself over to a pair of velvet armchairs. Next to them was a table upon which a towering silver Rumburgian tea urn had been set up.

LineNo: 10536588,

Beatrice Livingston (R): How are the princess' marriage pla...
en


"How are the princess' marriage plans coming along?"

LineNo: 10536714,

Player_Romus: Why? Is your eldest son single?
en


"Why? Is your eldest son single?"

LineNo: 10536816,

Player_Romus: I wouldn't know. I told her I won'...
en


"I wouldn't know. I told her I won't be arranging her marriage."

LineNo: 10536918,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Heavens, no. My Bradley is still b...
en


"Heavens, no. My Bradley is still betrothed to the Duchess of Thompsfort."

LineNo: 10537020,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Much as I'd like to continue our t...
en


"Much as I'd like to continue our tradition of royal intermarriage, this pairing is necessary to secure northwestern Rumburg's continued loyalty. Surely you understand."

LineNo: 10537146,

Player_Romus: A shame. They would have made beau...
en


"A shame. They would have made beautiful children."

LineNo: 10537248,

Player_Romus: Indeed. You made a wise arrangemen...
en


"Indeed. You made a wise arrangement."

LineNo: 10537350,

Player_Romus: I was joking. They're cousins, for...
en


"I was joking. They're cousins, for Dast's sake."

LineNo: 10537452,

Beatrice Livingston (R): That never stopped any of our nobl...
en


"That never stopped any of our noble ancestors."

LineNo: 10537554,

Beatrice Livingston (R): We royals are an endangered breed,...
en


"We royals are an endangered breed, you know. We've got to tend to our lineages as we would a rose garden."

LineNo: 10537680,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I'm sure you'll find just as suita...
en


"I'm sure you'll find just as suitable a match for my brilliant niece."

LineNo: 10537782,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Indeed they would have. But you'll...
en


"Indeed they would have. But you'll find another suitable a match for my brilliant niece, I'm sure."

LineNo: 10538154,

Player_Romus: It doesn't matter, anyway. I alrea...
en


"It doesn't matter, anyway. I already told her she can marry whomever she wants."

LineNo: 10538256,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Did you? My word.
en


"Did you? My word."

LineNo: 10538636,

Player_Romus: I'm on the lookout for candidates....
en


"I'm on the lookout for candidates. Someone from one of our other royal houses, perhaps."

LineNo: 10539008,

Player_Romus: You'll have to ask her yourself. W...
en


"You'll have to ask her yourself. We're not on the best terms these days."

LineNo: 10539110,

Player_Romus: Honestly, I have too much on my mi...
en


"Honestly, I have too much on my mind to even start to think about that."

LineNo: 10539212,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Very good. As you'll recall, I pro...
en


"Very good. As you'll recall, I promised my Bradley to the Duchess of Thompsfort to secure the loyalty of our country's northwestern regions."

LineNo: 10539314,

Beatrice Livingston (R): We royals are an endangered breed,...
en


"We royals are an endangered breed, you know. We've got to tend to our lineages as we would a rose garden."

LineNo: 10539432,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Oh? I'm sorry to hear that.
en


"Oh? I'm sorry to hear that."

LineNo: 10539534,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I lost my father at only 16, as yo...
en


"I lost my father at only 16, as you know. There were so many times over the years that I wished for his guidance."

LineNo: 10539636,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Well, don't dilly-dally much longe...
en


"Well, don't dilly-dally much longer. An unmarried royal is catnip for the tabloids."

LineNo: 10539738,

Beatrice Livingston (R): They had quite the field day with...
en


"They had quite the field day with my Bradley before I secured his betrothal."

LineNo: 10539864,

Player_Romus: If that means inbreeding, perhaps...
en


"If that means inbreeding, perhaps it's best to let the garden die."

LineNo: 10539966,

Player_Romus: I agree. But first cousins are too...
en


"I agree. But first cousins are too closely related for my comfort."

LineNo: 10540068,

Player_Romus: I don't see the harm in allowing a...
en


"I don't see the harm in allowing a few exotic plants to blossom here and there."

LineNo: 10540170,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Choose the wrong ones, and the wee...
en


"Choose the wrong ones, and the weeds will spread faster than you can pull them out."

LineNo: 10540272,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Better a cousin than a commoner, n...
en


"Better a cousin than a commoner, no?"

LineNo: 10540374,

Player_Romus: Fear not. The garden of House Tora...
en


"Fear not. The garden of House Toras shall remain in bloom for a long, long time."

LineNo: 10540476,

Player_Romus: If that means forcing my daughter...
en


"If that means forcing my daughter into an unhappy union, perhaps it's best to let the garden die."

LineNo: 10540578,

Beatrice Livingston (R): We royals are an endangered breed,...
en


"We royals are an endangered breed, you know. We've got to tend to our lineages as we would a rose garden."

LineNo: 10540696,

Player_Romus: Precisely my thinking. It's good t...
en


"Precisely my thinking. It's good to speak with someone who understands these things."

LineNo: 10540798,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Anytime, my dear brother-in-law.
en


"Anytime, my dear brother-in-law."

LineNo: 10540900,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You're lucky to have such a relati...
en


"You're lucky to have such a relationship in your life. Cherish it."

LineNo: 10541018,

Beatrice Livingston (R): With the help of House Livingston,...
en


"With the help of House Livingston, it shall bloom on only the richest of soil."

LineNo: 10541120,

Beatrice Livingston (R): If the garden dies, your ties to H...
en


"If the garden dies, your ties to House Livingston die with it."

LineNo: 10541222,

Princess Marriage Talk

Narrator: An informal supper with my sister-i...
en


An informal supper with my sister-in-law was scheduled for the evening. But for now, the protocol for an official diplomatic visit had to be observed.

LineNo: 10541522,

Player_Romus: She's on my council, you know.
en


"She's on my council, you know."

LineNo: 10541624,

Player_Romus: She's as stubborn as her mother wa...
en


"She's as stubborn as her mother was, that's for sure."

LineNo: 10542004,

Player_Romus: I wouldn't call her a 'lady''. She...
en


"I wouldn't call her a 'lady''. She's been neglecting her duties as princess."

LineNo: 10542106,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Oh, my. So young, and already prep...
en


"Oh, my. So young, and already preparing for the crown."

LineNo: 10542208,

Vina Toras: You were younger than me when you...
en


"You were younger than me when you got yours, weren't you?"

LineNo: 10542310,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Good girl. It's your royal obligat...
en


"Good girl. It's your royal obligation to give your father hell."

LineNo: 10542412,

Narrator: Vina laughed.
en


Vina laughed.

LineNo: 10542514,

Vina Toras: It's lovely to see you, Aunt Bea.
en


"It's lovely to see you, Aunt Bea."

LineNo: 10542616,

Narrator: Queen Beatrice gave Vina a mock ste...
en


Queen Beatrice gave Vina a mock stern look.

LineNo: 10542718,

Beatrice Livingston (R): It's your royal duty to give your...
en


"It's your royal duty to give your father hell. And it seems you're performing it admirably."

LineNo: 10542820,

Player_Romus: I am. And I know Lena would have b...
en


"I am. And I know Lena would have been, too."

LineNo: 10543200,

Narrator: Vina beamed.
en


Vina beamed.

LineNo: 10543302,

Narrator: Vina managed a weak smile.
en


Vina managed a weak smile.

LineNo: 10543404,

Narrator: The two women gave each other air k...
en


The two women gave each other air kisses, then stood back and eyed each other.

LineNo: 10543506,

Estela Toras: Is that so, Your Excellency?
en


"Is that so, Your Excellency?"

LineNo: 10543704,

Narrator: Beatrice motioned for her own atten...
en


Beatrice motioned for her own attendants to wait outside. We settled into our seats..

LineNo: 10543830,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I find your mother ever so charmin...
en


"I find your mother ever so charming. I never believed those nasty rumors about her one bit."

LineNo: 10543932,

Narrator: Queen Beatrice extended her little...
en


Queen Beatrice extended her little finger and took a sip from her own cup. She smiled approvingly.

LineNo: 10544040,

Beatrice Livingston (R): As you may know, Rumburg is curren...
en


"As you may know, Rumburg is currently a major importer of Wehzek oil."

LineNo: 10544142,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Our nations are bound by our share...
en


"Our nations are bound by our shared love for my sister. Such a relationship goes beyond mere transaction."

LineNo: 10544244,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Should you wish for something a li...
en


"Should you wish for something a little less subtle, I have a suggestion."

LineNo: 10544442,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Of course, an immediate modernizat...
en


"Of course, an immediate modernization of your Monqiz port would be required to handle the excess shipping traffic."

LineNo: 10544552,

Player_Romus: We always try to stay ahead.
en


"We always try to stay ahead."

LineNo: 10544654,

Player_Romus: I love it. You buy less oil from W...
en


"I love it. You buy less oil from Wehlen, and we'll make up the difference with natural gas and other energy sources."

LineNo: 10544756,

Player_Romus: That's a lot to demand for a plan...
en


"That's a lot to demand for a plan that may not even be useful or necessary."

LineNo: 10544858,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I'm quite sure some of the same sh...
en


"I'm quite sure some of the same ships that carry out our gold trade can be retrofitted to transport natural gas in its liquified form."

LineNo: 10544960,

Player_Romus: That can be arranged.
en


"That can be arranged."

LineNo: 10545062,

Player_Romus: No, I'm satisfied with our countri...
en


"No, I'm satisfied with our countries' current trade relations. I don't want to complicate them."

LineNo: 10545164,

Player_Romus: Interesting. But how would Rizian...
en


"Interesting. But how would Rizian gas even reach Rumburg from here?"

LineNo: 10545266,

Player_Romus: Would we have to replace all the o...
en


"Would we have to replace all the oil you've been purchasing? What about only part of it?"

LineNo: 10545368,

Player_Romus: So you believe Wehlen can't find a...
en


"So you believe Wehlen can't find another customer?"

LineNo: 10545470,

Player_Romus: This is a serious promise. What ha...
en


"This is a serious promise. What happens if I can't keep up my end of the guarantee?"

LineNo: 10545572,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Rumburg would prefer to eliminate...
en


"Rumburg would prefer to eliminate its energy dependence on Wehlen entirely."

LineNo: 10545674,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Believe it or not, Wiktor Smolak h...
en


"Believe it or not, Wiktor Smolak has managed to alienate Wehlen from most of its neighbors."

LineNo: 10545776,

Beatrice Livingston (R): We'll have to find a more reliable...
en


"We'll have to find a more reliable trading partner. For energy as well as other materials."

LineNo: 10545878,

Beatrice Livingston (R): And? What do you think of the idea?
en


"And? What do you think of the idea?"

LineNo: 10546004,

Player_Romus: I can't promise you anything right...
en


"I can't promise you anything right now, Your Excellency. But I'll keep your offer in mind as Rizia expands its energy horizons."

LineNo: 10546106,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Thrilling. How much less oil, then?
en


"Thrilling. How much less oil, then?"

LineNo: 10546224,

Player_Romus: Can you halve your imports? We wil...
en


"Can you halve your imports? We will provide some from our stockpiles now and more in the future."

LineNo: 10546230,

Player_Romus: Can you halve your imports? We wil...
Menu Text en


"Can you halve your imports? We will provide some from our stockpiles now and more in the future." [-2 Energy, -1 Energy Per Turn]

LineNo: 10546332,

Player_Romus: Screw it, Your Excellency. Cut off...
en


"Screw it, Your Excellency. Cut off Wehlen completely."

LineNo: 10546338,

Player_Romus: Screw it, Your Excellency. Cut off...
Menu Text en


"Screw it, Your Excellency. Cut off Wehlen completely." [-3 Energy, -2 Energy Per Turn]

LineNo: 10546440,

Narrator: Beatrice smiled.
en


Beatrice smiled.

LineNo: 10546542,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Very bold of you. My sister didn't...
en


"Very bold of you. My sister didn't marry a man who takes half measures."

LineNo: 10546644,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Very well, Your Majesty. Of course...
en


"Very well, Your Majesty. Of course we'd appreciate any help stoking our hungry furnaces."

LineNo: 10546746,

Beatrice Livingston (R): That's understandable. Do reach ou...
en


"That's understandable. Do reach out if you change your mind. Bilateral relations always need maintaining."

LineNo: 10546938,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I can see. We are already a few st...
en


"I can see. We are already a few steps ahead."

LineNo: 10547040,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Even if you don't ship us gas, get...
en


"Even if you don't ship us gas, getting that port into tip-top shape would make our gold trade more efficient."

LineNo: 10547142,

Beatrice Livingston (R): If we were to significantly reduce...
en


"If we were to significantly reduce our imports, the financial pressure -- and thus your leverage over Wehlen -- would be considerable."

LineNo: 10547268,

Player_Romus: Wait. How much oil are you importi...
en


"Wait. How much oil are you importing from Wehlen?"

LineNo: 10547370,

Player_Romus: I thought you hated Wehlen. But yo...
en


"I thought you hated Wehlen. But you're buying their oil?"

LineNo: 10547472,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Don't look so shocked. It's a part...
en


"Don't look so shocked. It's a partnership of convenience."

LineNo: 10547574,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Enough to seriously make a dent in...
